To find the greatest common factor (GCF) of two integers a and b, we can use the following recursive algorithm:

1. If a is evenly divisible by b, then the GCF is b.
2. If a is not evenly divisible by b, then the GCF of a and b is equal to the GCF of b and the remainder when a is divided by b.

We can implement this algorithm in Java as follows:
```java
public static int gcf(int a, int b) {
    if (b == 0) {
        return a;
    }
    return gcf(b, a % b);
}
```
This method takes two integers a and b as parameters and returns the GCF of a and b using the recursive algorithm described above. The method first checks if b is 0. If so, then a is the GCF, since there is no other divisor. Otherwise, the method calls itself with b and the remainder of a divided by b (a % b). This continues recursively until the base case is reached (when b is 0), at which point the GCF is returned.

